Class StripeFileParams

  • com.stripe.android.model.StripeFileParams

  • public class StripeFileParams

    Create a file

    To upload a file to Stripe, you’ll need to send a request of type multipart/form-data. The request should contain the file you would like to upload, as well as the parameters for creating a file.

                        java.io.File file,

        Create a file

        To upload a file to Stripe, you’ll need to send a request of type multipart/form-data. The request should contain the file you would like to upload, as well as the parameters for creating a file.

        Parameters:
        file - A file to upload. The file should follow the specifications of RFC 2388 (which defines filetransfers for the multipart/form-data protocol).
        purpose -

        The purpose of the uploaded file. Possible values are business_icon, business_logo, customer_signature, dispute_evidence, identity_document, pci_document, or tax_document_user_upload.

        purpose
